Known bugs and fragile areas.


RARE XSAN CRASH IN JIT DISPATCH (UNRESOLVED)

Under ASan, the ARM64 JIT very rarely (~1 in 1000+ runs) SEGVs on a
data read near a page boundary during test_fma_f32.  Audit of the JIT
codegen shows all vector-width loads are guarded by the remaining >= K
branch, and scalar tail loads are single-element.  Guard pages have been
added after JIT code allocations to catch code overruns.

The crash may be an ASan redzone/quarantine artifact rather than a real
overread.  Cannot reproduce reliably.
